    About this item

    • AIR CONDUCTION TECHNOLOGY: Air conduction offers a more natural sound with a full frequency range, delivering clearer and safer sound to your ear than traditional headphones. Enjoy music, audiobooks, and podcasts with crisp sound and balanced bass.
    • ANYTIME, ANYWHERE: Enjoy 7 hours of playtime from a 2-hours full charge, with an extra 21 hours from the case. Need a quick boost? Just 5 minutes in the case gives you an extra hour. And mono mode lets you use one earbud while the other charges.
    • FIT WITH YOUR MOVEMENT: These open-ear earbuds eliminate the need for different-sized ear tips. Comfortable ear hooks loop around your ears, and a rubberized anchor at the end gently grips behind your ear for a secure and comfortable fit.
    • BORN TO SPORTS: Designed for intense workouts, dusty trails, and rainy runs, these headphones feature an IP55 rating for moisture and dust resistance. With a bright LED light design, you'll stay visible in low-light conditions.
    • BLUETOOTH MULTIPOINT: The air conduction headphones can connect to 2 Bluetooth devices at once. Great if you're listening to music on your phone and getting training notifications from your smartwatch. Ready to pair as soon as you turn them on
    • TOUCH OR APP CONTROL: Answer calls, pause music and wake your voice assistant with a simple button press. With the PHILIPS headphones app, you can choose from preset listening styles or use the equalizer to fine-tune the sounds to suit your workout.

          How customer reviews and ratings work

          Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

          Amazon Customer
          5 out of 5 stars
          Comfortable and doesn't fatigue my ears
          You get the earbuds, the charging case and a usb c to usb a cable. The case itself is pretty lightweight as are the earbuds. They don't weigh down my ears or cause any fatigue and stay in place pretty well. There really is no way to adjust them to get a "better fit" but they fit my ears fine as is. I am no audiophile but I am surprised by how good these sounded. There is a fully functional app that allows you to EQ them for better sound quality. It doesn't go in ear so it doesn't block out sound that much but it gets loud enough that I can't hear my surroundings. There is a red light on each earbud which can help with visibility while cycling or running at night. While you can not control the color you can control the blinking speed or choose to have it on constantly. You can also remap the touch controls from the app.

          • Mr. P
            4.0 out of 5 stars Very comfortable with good sound. Easy to set up.
            Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2025
            Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
            I got these for use at the gym. I already have a nice pair of BT earbuds, but they tend to wiggle loose if I am running too fast during a workout. The over the ear style of these are a great upgrade in that respect. These are not going anywhere. The only downside to the over the ear style is they interfere with the arms on my glasses. Not a big deal at the gym since I don't need my glasses, but they aren't great for outdoor use since I run into the same problem with sunglasses.

            I also tried wearing them while mowing the lawn. The open ear design is a big drawback here since they don't block any outside noise. I had to crank up the volume to hear my music over the mower.

            The initial pairing process was super easy, and they are always detected by my phone whenever I take them out of their case.

            These will be my regular gym earbuds. I am very happy with them for that setting. For other settings, especially outdoors, I'll stick with my old in ear buds.

          • mostlyharmlessx
            5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent comfort and sound with lots of features!
            Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2025
            Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
            These are just excellent earsets, really great design and sound!

            Setup is simple. These come in a nice compact case that is also a charging case, so they came charged and ready to test. Inside the lid of the case is a scan code for the Philips app, which offers access to different EQ settings, control programming and other features like turning on the flashing lights on the earsets for more visibility while running. By default, I found the sound decent enough for music or podcasts or calls, so you can get by without the app. However, there is quite a bit of additional functionality that these have that you will miss out on without the app, most of all the instructions on how to control features with gestures/taps. I have other earbuds where taps or double taps allow you do different things like answer calls, skip to next track, etc, but it's not easy to remember them all. The app here has all the controls listed out for the left and right earset. You can do multi-device pairing with these and there is also a low latency mode which can help if the audio is a little behind a video you are watching, though I have not seen a problem with that myself.

            The design of these is comfortable, with hardly any noticeable weight on the ears. They stay in place well even with fairly vigorous movement like running or even hitting some tennis balls against the backboard. The sound has a nice depth even at default, and you have several eq presets as well as a custom one you can set to tailor the sound to your needs. While the sound of these is clear and decent, they also allow you to hear sounds around you at all times clearly. Great balance of sound and awareness!

            Voice calls are decent, and I can hear folks pretty clearly and they claim they can hear me ok as well. There was some slight breeze on my end while testing calls, but the person on the other end had no trouble understanding me. Music sounds rich and full for the open design, and podcasts are clear. I tested with the default sound and also the different EQ settings. Each setting actually makes a decent difference, whether you want more bass or more treble or clearer voice. At the end, I've left these on the default setting as it's good for my needs. You can actually control things like the running lights without the app, and you can also set what the different gestures can do to tailor them to your use. Lots of control over features with the apps, but once things are set you don't need to fiddle in there unless you want to.

            Bluetooth connection has been stable, even cross-body in a pocket or a couple of rooms away from an iphone 15 pro. Battery life is good for several hours, and the charging case allows you to charge these up on the go at a fairly decent charging speed. I don't usually run things to very low charge, but it's been easy to keep these powered up and they recharge just fine in an hour or two from less than 50%. Keeping them clean is easy, since they don't actually go inside your ear, just wipe them off if you get them sweaty.

            Overall, solid sounding and comfortable product with lots of features and a decent app. Worth the listed price!

          About this Item

          • AIR CONDUCTION TECHNOLOGY: Air conduction offers a more natural sound with a full frequency range, delivering clearer and safer sound to your ear than traditional headphones. Enjoy music, audiobooks, and podcasts with crisp sound and balanced bass.
          • ANYTIME, ANYWHERE: Enjoy 7 hours of playtime from a 2-hours full charge, with an extra 21 hours from the case. Need a quick boost? Just 5 minutes in the case gives you an extra hour. And mono mode lets you use one earbud while the other charges.
          • FIT WITH YOUR MOVEMENT: These open-ear earbuds eliminate the need for different-sized ear tips. Comfortable ear hooks loop around your ears, and a rubberized anchor at the end gently grips behind your ear for a secure and comfortable fit.
          • BORN TO SPORTS: Designed for intense workouts, dusty trails, and rainy runs, these headphones feature an IP55 rating for moisture and dust resistance. With a bright LED light design, you'll stay visible in low-light conditions.
          • BLUETOOTH MULTIPOINT: The air conduction headphones can connect to 2 Bluetooth devices at once. Great if you're listening to music on your phone and getting training notifications from your smartwatch. Ready to pair as soon as you turn them on
          • TOUCH OR APP CONTROL: Answer calls, pause music and wake your voice assistant with a simple button press. With the PHILIPS headphones app, you can choose from preset listening styles or use the equalizer to fine-tune the sounds to suit your workout.

          Product Description

          Go for it with the true wireless open-ear buds that always fit perfectly! A soft, comfy hook keeps these buds in place no matter how you love to moveand the open-ear design means youll hear your world as well as your music.
